  "response": "No, microwave ovens are designed with safety features that immediately stop the generation of microwaves when the door is opened. Modern microwave ovens have multiple safety interlocks that cut power to the magnetron (the component that produces microwaves) as soon as the door is opened. This means that when you open the door before the beep, no harmful radiation will be released. The microwave radiation is contained within the oven when it's operating, and the door mechanism ensures it stops when the door is opened.",
